This paper deals with knowledge distillation in the context of image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of adversarial training is also a key aspect of the paper, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the transfer of knowledge between multiple networks, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper applies its method to various network architectures, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
